{"id":138,"parent_id":132,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":138,"title":"2 Corinthians 12-13: Paul Is Caught Up into the Third Heaven","subtitle":"","short_title":"2 Corinthians 12-13: Paul Is Caught Up into the Third Heaven","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven"},[".heading",{"id":"head7","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.head7"},["h1","2Corinthians 12–13"],[".subtitle","Paul Is Caught Up into the Third Heaven"],[".intro","Paul wrote that he was “caught up to the third heaven” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/12.2"},"2 Corinthians 12:2"],")—the celestial kingdom. In 1836 the Prophet Joseph Smith also had a vision of the celestial kingdom. He wrote:"],[".intro","“I saw the transcendent beauty of the gate through which the heirs of that kingdom will enter, which was like unto circling flames of fire;"],[".intro","“Also the blazing throne of God, whereon was seated the Father and the Son."],[".intro","“I saw the beautiful streets of that kingdom, which had the appearance of being paved with gold” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/137.2-4"},"D&C 137:2–4"],")."]],[".bodyBlock",[".",{"id":"f22","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.f22"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-130-2.gif"}]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f23","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.f23"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/12"},"2 Corinthians 12"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Unspeakable"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Indescribable, perhaps too holy to be talked about"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Buffet"],"(v. 7)"],["td","Mistreat"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Bewail"],"(v. 21)"],["td","Mourn for"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Lasciviousness"],"(v. 21)"],["td","Unbridled lust"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/12.2"},"2 Corinthians 12:2"],"—Paul Sees the Celestial Kingdom"],["p.para",{"id":"p77","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.p77"},"Elder Bruce R. McConkie said: “Speaking of himself, Paul says he was ‘caught up to the third heaven,’ which is the celestial kingdom” (",["span.emphasis","The Mortal Messiah,"],"4:394)."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/12.7"},"2 Corinthians 12:7"],"—“A Thorn in the Flesh”"],["p.para",{"id":"p78","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.p78"},"Neither the scriptures nor modern revelation tells us what “thorn in the flesh” afflicted or tormented Paul. Many believe Paul was afflicted with a physical disability that hindered his missionary labors."],[".figure",{"id":"f24","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.f24"},["p"],["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/13"},"2 Corinthians 13"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Reprobates"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Those who are unworthy or fail the test"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","To edification, and not to destruction"],"(v. 10)"],["td","To strengthen you, and not to condemn you"],["td"]]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/13.1"},"2 Corinthians 13:1"],"—“Two or Three Witnesses”"],["p.para",{"id":"p81","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.p81"},"God always provides more than one witness to support His words. This is called the law of witnesses (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/11.3-4"},"2 Nephi 11:3–4"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/6.28"},"D&C 6:28"],"). Even today priesthood ordinances must be performed with more than one witness present."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/13.12"},"2 Corinthians 13:12"],"—“Greet One Another with an Holy Kiss”"],["p.para",{"id":"p82","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.p82"},"The Joseph Smith Translation changes the word",["span.emphasis","kiss"],"to",["span.emphasis","salutation,"],"meaning a warm greeting."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p83","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.p83"},"Do activities A and B as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/12"},"2 Corinthians 12–13"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Unlock the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f25","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.f25"},["p.preamble","Read the following pairs of scriptures and explain how the first scripture helps you better understand Paul’s teachings in the second scripture:"],["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/137.1-5"},"Doctrine and Covenants 137:1–5"],"and",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/12.1-4"},"2 Corinthians 12:1–4"]]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.27"},"Ether 12:27"],"and",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/12.5-10"},"2 Corinthians 12:5–10"]]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"Choose a Favorite Verse"],["p.para",{"id":"p86","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-second-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-corinthians/2-corinthians-12-13-paul-is-caught-up-into-the-third-heaven.p86"},"As you read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/2-cor/13"},"2 Corinthians 13"],", choose a verse that stands out to you as being very important. Write that verse in your notebook and tell why you chose it."]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
